The paper proposes a new supervised layer-wise pretraining strategy for initializing Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) in the context of RNN-based classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions benchmarks from the domains of Speech Recognition and Remote Sensing, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could also be relevant sub-categories.
